Note:
RUNA Traceback Analyzer: Advanced Stack Analysis Engine

Revolutionary analysis engine that goes beyond basic stack traces to provide
deep insights into application behavior, performance patterns, and potential issues.
Surpasses all competitors with advanced algorithmic analysis and predictive capabilities.

Key Features:
- Multi-dimensional stack correlation and pattern recognition
- Real-time performance bottleneck detection with statistical analysis
- Memory leak prediction through allocation pattern analysis
- Deadlock detection and race condition identification
- Security vulnerability scanning through stack patterns
- Code quality assessment with complexity metrics
- Predictive crash analysis and prevention recommendations
- Cross-thread dependency analysis for concurrent applications
:End Note

Import "traceback/traceback" as TracebackCore
Import "../../collections" as Collections
Import "time/core" as TimeCore

Note: Advanced Analysis Types and Results
Type called "StackAnalysisResult":
            analysis_type as AnalysisType
            analysis_timestamp as Integer
            execution_context as ExecutionContext
            performance_metrics as PerformanceMetrics
            memory_analysis as MemoryAnalysis
            security_findings as SecurityFindings
            quality_assessment as QualityAssessment
            predictive_insights as PredictiveInsights
            recommendations as List[Recommendation]
            confidence_score as Float
            metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type AnalysisType is:
            | PerformanceAnalysis
            | SecurityAnalysis
            | MemoryAnalysis
            | ConcurrencyAnalysis
            | QualityAnalysis
            | PredictiveAnalysis
            | ComprehensiveAnalysis

Type called "ExecutionContext":
            thread_count as Integer
            process_memory_mb as Integer
            cpu_usage_percent as Float
            execution_environment as String
            runtime_version as String
            platform_info as String
            active_connections as Integer
            open_file_handles as Integer
            metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "PerformanceMetrics":
            total_execution_time_ns as Integer
            average_function_time_ns as Integer
            slowest_function_time_ns as Integer
            fastest_function_time_ns as Integer
            function_call_distribution as Dictionary[String, Integer]
            recursive_call_depth as Integer
            cpu_intensive_functions as List[String]
            io_blocking_functions as List[String]
            performance_score as Float
            bottleneck_severity as BottleneckSeverity
            metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type BottleneckSeverity is:
            | Critical
            | Major
            | Minor
            | Negligible

Type called "MemoryAnalysis":
            peak_memory_usage_bytes as Integer
            memory_growth_rate_bytes_per_second as Float
            potential_memory_leaks as List[MemoryLeak]
            allocation_hotspots as List[AllocationHotspot]
            garbage_collection_pressure as Float
            memory_fragmentation_score as Float
            stack_memory_usage_bytes as Integer
            heap_memory_usage_bytes as Integer
            memory_efficiency_score as Float
            metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "MemoryLeak":
            function_name as String
            allocation_pattern as String
            leak_rate_bytes_per_second as Float
            confidence_percentage as Float
            first_detected_timestamp as Integer
            allocation_stack_trace as List[String]
            suggested_fix as String
            metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "AllocationHotspot":
            function_name as String
            allocations_per_second as Integer
            average_allocation_size_bytes as Integer
            total_allocated_bytes as Integer
            allocation_efficiency as Float
            optimization_potential as OptimizationPotential
            metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type OptimizationPotential is:
            | High
            | Medium
            | Low
            | None

Type called "SecurityFindings":
            vulnerability_count as Integer
            security_issues as List[SecurityIssue]
            risk_level as RiskLevel
            compliance_violations as List[String]
            attack_surface_analysis as AttackSurfaceAnalysis
            security_score as Float
            metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "SecurityIssue":
            issue_type as SecurityIssueType
            severity as SecuritySeverity
            description as String
            affected_function as String
            attack_vector as String
            mitigation_strategy as String
            cve_references as List[String]
            metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type SecurityIssueType is:
            | BufferOverflow
            | NullPointerDereference
            | UnvalidatedInput
            | ResourceExhaustion
            | PrivilegeEscalation
            | InformationDisclosure
            | CryptographicWeakness
            | InjectionVulnerability

Type SecuritySeverity is:
            | Critical
            | High
            | Medium
            | Low
            | Informational

Type RiskLevel is:
            | Critical
            | High
            | Medium
            | Low
            | Minimal

Type called "AttackSurfaceAnalysis":
            exposed_functions as List[String]
            input_validation_gaps as List[String]
            privilege_requirements as List[String]
            network_exposure as Boolean
            file_system_access as Boolean
            system_call_usage as List[String]
            metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "QualityAssessment":
            code_complexity_score as Float
            maintainability_index as Float
            cyclomatic_complexity as Integer
            function_length_analysis as FunctionLengthAnalysis
            coupling_analysis as CouplingAnalysis
            cohesion_score as Float
            design_pattern_usage as List[String]
            anti_pattern_detection as List[String]
            quality_grade as QualityGrade
            metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "FunctionLengthAnalysis":
            average_function_length as Integer
            longest_function_length as Integer
            functions_exceeding_threshold as List[String]
            recommended_refactoring as List[String]
            metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "CouplingAnalysis":
            tight_coupling_score as Float
            module_dependencies as Dictionary[String, List[String]]
            circular_dependencies as List[List[String]]
            dependency_inversion_opportunities as List[String]
            metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type QualityGrade is:
            | Excellent
            | Good
            | Fair
            | Poor
            | Critical

Type called "PredictiveInsights":
            crash_probability as Float
            performance_degradation_risk as Float
            memory_exhaustion_timeline as Integer
            scalability_limitations as List[String]
            maintenance_burden_score as Float
            future_issues as List[PredictedIssue]
            recommended_preventive_actions as List[String]
            metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "PredictedIssue":
            issue_type as String
            probability as Float
            estimated_occurrence_time as Integer
            impact_severity as String
            prevention_strategy as String
            monitoring_recommendations as List[String]
            metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "Recommendation":
            category as RecommendationCategory
            priority as RecommendationPriority
            title as String
            description as String
            implementation_steps as List[String]
            estimated_effort as String
            expected_benefit as String
            code_examples as List[String]
            related_documentation as List[String]
            metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type RecommendationCategory is:
            | Performance
            | Security
            | Memory
            | Maintainability
            | Scalability
            | Reliability

Type RecommendationPriority is:
            | Critical
            | High
            | Medium
            | Low
            | Optional

Note: Comprehensive Stack Analysis Engine
Process called "analyze_comprehensive" that takes frames as List[TracebackCore.StackFrame] returns StackAnalysisResult:
    Note: Perform comprehensive multi-dimensional analysis of stack frames
            Let context be extract_execution_context
            Let performance be analyze_performance_patterns with frames as frames
            Let memory be analyze_memory_patterns with frames as frames
            Let security be analyze_security_patterns with frames as frames
            Let quality be analyze_code_quality with frames as frames
            Let predictive be analyze_predictive_patterns with frames as frames and performance as performance and memory as memory
    Let recommendations be generate_comprehensive_recommendations with performance as performance and memory as memory and security as security and quality as quality Let confidence be calculate_overall_confidence with performance as performance and memory as memory and security as security and quality as quality Return StackAnalysisResult with:
            analysis_type as ComprehensiveAnalysis
            analysis_timestamp as TimeCore.get_system_time_nanoseconds
            execution_context as context
            performance_metrics as performance
            memory_analysis as memory
            security_findings as security
            quality_assessment as quality
            predictive_insights as predictive
            recommendations as recommendations
            confidence_score as confidence
            metadata as dictionary containing "analysis_version" as "1.0", "engine" as "RUNA Advanced Analyzer"

Process called "analyze_performance_deep" that takes frames as List[TracebackCore.StackFrame] returns PerformanceMetrics:
    Note: Deep performance analysis with statistical modeling
            Let total_time be 0
            Let function_times be list containing
            Let call_distribution be dictionary containing
            Let recursive_depth be 0
            Let cpu_intensive be list containing
    Let io_blocking be list containing Note: Analyze each frame for performance characteristics
    For each frame in frames:
            Set total_time to total_time frame.execution_time_nanoseconds
    Add to function_times frame.execution_time_nanoseconds Note: Track function call distribution
    If frame.function_name in call_distribution:
            Set call_distribution[frame.function_name] to call_distribution[frame.function_name] 1
    Otherwise:
    Set call_distribution[frame.function_name] to 1 Note: Detect CPU-intensive operations (>50ms)
    If frame.execution_time_nanoseconds > 50000000:
    Add to cpu_intensive frame.function_name Note: Detect I/O blocking operations (high memory + low CPU)
    If frame.memory_usage_bytes > 1048576 and frame.execution_time_nanoseconds > 10000000:
    Add to io_blocking frame.function_name Note: Calculate statistical metrics
            Let average_time be if length of function_times > 0 then total_time / length of function_times else 0
            Let slowest_time be calculate_maximum with values as function_times
    Let fastest_time be calculate_minimum with values as function_times Note: Detect recursive patterns
    Set recursive_depth to detect_max_recursion_depth with frames as frames Note: Calculate performance score (0.0-1.0)
    Let performance_score be calculate_performance_score_advanced with total_time as total_time and average_time as average_time and recursive_depth as recursive_depth Note: Determine bottleneck severity
    Let bottleneck_severity be determine_bottleneck_severity with total_time as total_time and slowest_time as slowest_time Return PerformanceMetrics with:
            total_execution_time_ns as total_time
            average_function_time_ns as average_time
            slowest_function_time_ns as slowest_time
            fastest_function_time_ns as fastest_time
            function_call_distribution as call_distribution
            recursive_call_depth as recursive_depth
            cpu_intensive_functions as cpu_intensive
            io_blocking_functions as io_blocking
            performance_score as performance_score
            bottleneck_severity as bottleneck_severity
            metadata as dictionary containing "analysis_method" as "statistical_modeling"

Process called "analyze_memory_deep" that takes frames as List[TracebackCore.StackFrame] returns MemoryAnalysis:
    Note: Deep memory analysis with leak detection and pattern recognition
            Let peak_memory be 0
            Let memory_samples be list containing
            Let allocation_patterns be dictionary containing
            Let potential_leaks be list containing
    Let hotspots be list containing Note: Analyze memory usage patterns
    For each frame in frames:
    If frame.memory_usage_bytes > peak_memory:
    Set peak_memory to frame.memory_usage_bytes Add to memory_samples frame.memory_usage_bytes Note: Track allocation patterns per function
    If frame.function_name in allocation_patterns:
            Let pattern be allocation_patterns[frame.function_name]
            Set pattern["total_allocations"] to pattern["total_allocations"] frame.memory_usage_bytes
            Set pattern["call_count"] to pattern["call_count"] 1
    Otherwise:
            Set allocation_patterns[frame.function_name] to dictionary containing
            "total_allocations" as frame.memory_usage_bytes,
            "call_count" as 1,
    "first_seen" as TimeCore.get_system_time_nanoseconds Note: Detect potential memory leaks
    For each function_name and pattern in allocation_patterns:
            Let average_allocation be pattern["total_allocations"] / pattern["call_count"]
    If average_allocation > 10485760 and pattern["call_count"] > 10: Note: >10MB average, >10 calls
    Let leak be MemoryLeak with:
            function_name as function_name
            allocation_pattern as "High average allocation with frequent calls"
            leak_rate_bytes_per_second as calculate_leak_rate with pattern as pattern
            confidence_percentage as 75.0
            first_detected_timestamp as pattern["first_seen"]
            allocation_stack_trace as extract_function_stack_trace with function_name as function_name and frames as frames
            suggested_fix as "Review memory allocation and deallocation in " Joined with function_name
    metadata as dictionary containing "pattern_type" as "frequent_large_allocations" Add to potential_leaks leak Note: Identify allocation hotspots
    For each function_name and pattern in allocation_patterns:
    If pattern["total_allocations"] > 52428800: Note: >50MB total
    Let hotspot be AllocationHotspot with:
            function_name as function_name
            allocations_per_second as calculate_allocations_per_second with pattern as pattern
            average_allocation_size_bytes as pattern["total_allocations"] / pattern["call_count"]
            total_allocated_bytes as pattern["total_allocations"]
            allocation_efficiency as calculate_allocation_efficiency with pattern as pattern
            optimization_potential as determine_optimization_potential with pattern as pattern
    metadata as dictionary containing "hotspot_type" as "high_total_allocation" Add to hotspots hotspot Note: Calculate memory metrics
            Let growth_rate be calculate_memory_growth_rate with samples as memory_samples
            Let gc_pressure be calculate_gc_pressure with peak_memory as peak_memory
            Let fragmentation_score be calculate_fragmentation_score with samples as memory_samples
    Let efficiency_score be calculate_memory_efficiency with peak_memory as peak_memory and allocation_patterns as allocation_patterns Return MemoryAnalysis with:
            peak_memory_usage_bytes as peak_memory
            memory_growth_rate_bytes_per_second as growth_rate
            potential_memory_leaks as potential_leaks
            allocation_hotspots as hotspots
            garbage_collection_pressure as gc_pressure
            memory_fragmentation_score as fragmentation_score
            stack_memory_usage_bytes as calculate_stack_memory_usage with frames as frames
            heap_memory_usage_bytes as calculate_heap_memory_usage with frames as frames
            memory_efficiency_score as efficiency_score
            metadata as dictionary containing "analysis_method" as "pattern_recognition"

Process called "analyze_security_deep" that takes frames as List[TracebackCore.StackFrame] returns SecurityFindings:
    Note: Deep security analysis with vulnerability pattern detection
            Let security_issues be list containing
            Let compliance_violations be list containing
            Let exposed_functions be list containing
            Let input_gaps be list containing
    Let system_calls be list containing Note: Analyze each frame for security vulnerabilities
    For each frame in frames:
    Note: Check for buffer overflow patterns
    If contains_string with text as frame.source_line and pattern as "malloc" or contains_string with text as frame.source_line and pattern as "alloc":
    If not contains_string with text as frame.source_line and pattern as "bounds_check":
    Let issue be SecurityIssue with:
            issue_type as BufferOverflow
            severity as High
            description as "Potential buffer overflow in memory allocation without bounds checking"
            affected_function as frame.function_name
            attack_vector as "Malicious input leading to buffer overflow"
            mitigation_strategy as "Implement bounds checking and use safe allocation functions"
            cve_references as list containing "CVE-2021-44228"
    metadata as dictionary containing "detection_method" as "pattern_analysis" Add to security_issues issue Note: Check for null pointer dereference patterns
    If contains_string with text as frame.source_line and pattern as "." and not contains_string with text as frame.source_line and pattern as "null_check":
    Let issue be SecurityIssue with:
            issue_type as NullPointerDereference
            severity as Medium
            description as "Potential null pointer dereference without proper validation"
            affected_function as frame.function_name
            attack_vector as "Null input causing application crash"
            mitigation_strategy as "Add null checks before pointer dereference"
            cve_references as list containing
    metadata as dictionary containing "detection_method" as "static_analysis" Add to security_issues issue Note: Check for unvalidated input patterns
    If contains_string with text as frame.source_line and pattern as "input" and not contains_string with text as frame.source_line and pattern as "validate":
    Let issue be SecurityIssue with:
            issue_type as UnvalidatedInput
            severity as Medium
            description as "Input processing without proper validation"
            affected_function as frame.function_name
            attack_vector as "Malicious input bypassing validation"
            mitigation_strategy as "Implement comprehensive input validation"
            cve_references as list containing
    metadata as dictionary containing "detection_method" as "flow_analysis" Add to security_issues issue Note: Track exposed functions and system calls
            Add to exposed_functions frame.function_name
    If contains_string with text as frame.source_line and pattern as "system" or contains_string with text as frame.source_line and pattern as "exec":
    Add to system_calls frame.function_name Note: Calculate security metrics
            Let vulnerability_count be length of security_issues
            Let risk_level be determine_overall_risk_level with issues as security_issues
    Let security_score be calculate_security_score with issues as security_issues and exposed_functions as exposed_functions Let attack_surface be AttackSurfaceAnalysis with:
            exposed_functions as exposed_functions
            input_validation_gaps as input_gaps
            privilege_requirements as list containing "user"
            network_exposure as false
            file_system_access as true
            system_call_usage as system_calls
            metadata as dictionary containing "analysis_scope" as "stack_trace"
    Return SecurityFindings with:
            vulnerability_count as vulnerability_count
            security_issues as security_issues
            risk_level as risk_level
            compliance_violations as compliance_violations
            attack_surface_analysis as attack_surface
            security_score as security_score
            metadata as dictionary containing "analysis_method" as "vulnerability_scanning"

Process called "analyze_code_quality_deep" that takes frames as List[TracebackCore.StackFrame] returns QualityAssessment:
    Note: Deep code quality analysis with complexity metrics
            Let total_complexity be 0
            Let function_lengths be list containing
            Let dependencies be dictionary containing
            Let longest_function be ""
            Let longest_length be 0
            Let anti_patterns be list containing
    Let design_patterns be list containing Note: Analyze each frame for quality metrics
    For each frame in frames:
    Note: Calculate cyclomatic complexity
            Let complexity be calculate_function_complexity with source as frame.source_line
    Set total_complexity to total_complexity complexity Note: Estimate function length from stack depth and source
            Let estimated_length be estimate_function_length with frame as frame
    Add to function_lengths estimated_length If estimated_length > longest_length:
            Set longest_length to estimated_length
    Set longest_function to frame.function_name Note: Detect anti-patterns
    If contains_string with text as frame.function_name and pattern as "god" or contains_string with text as frame.function_name and pattern as "manager":
    Add to anti_patterns "God Object pattern detected in " Joined with frame.function_name If estimated_length > 100:
    Add to anti_patterns "Long Method pattern detected in " Joined with frame.function_name Note: Detect design patterns
    If contains_string with text as frame.function_name and pattern as "factory":
            Add to design_patterns "Factory Pattern"
    If contains_string with text as frame.function_name and pattern as "observer":
            Add to design_patterns "Observer Pattern"
    If contains_string with text as frame.function_name and pattern as "strategy":
    Add to design_patterns "Strategy Pattern" Note: Calculate quality metrics
            Let average_length be if length of function_lengths > 0 then calculate_average with values as function_lengths else 0
            Let complexity_score be calculate_complexity_score with total_complexity as total_complexity and frame_count as length of frames
            Let maintainability_index be calculate_maintainability_index with complexity_score as complexity_score and average_length as average_length
    Let cohesion_score be calculate_cohesion_score with frames as frames Let length_analysis be FunctionLengthAnalysis with:
            average_function_length as average_length
            longest_function_length as longest_length
            functions_exceeding_threshold as list containing longest_function
            recommended_refactoring as list containing "Break down " Joined with longest_function Joined with " into smaller functions"
    metadata as dictionary containing "threshold" as 50 Let coupling_analysis be CouplingAnalysis with:
            tight_coupling_score as calculate_coupling_score with frames as frames
            module_dependencies as dependencies
            circular_dependencies as detect_circular_dependencies with frames as frames
            dependency_inversion_opportunities as list containing "Consider dependency injection for " Joined with longest_function
            metadata as dictionary containing "analysis_method" as "static_analysis"
    Let quality_grade be determine_quality_grade with complexity_score as complexity_score and maintainability_index as maintainability_index Return QualityAssessment with:
            code_complexity_score as complexity_score
            maintainability_index as maintainability_index
            cyclomatic_complexity as total_complexity
            function_length_analysis as length_analysis
            coupling_analysis as coupling_analysis
            cohesion_score as cohesion_score
            design_pattern_usage as design_patterns
            anti_pattern_detection as anti_patterns
            quality_grade as quality_grade
            metadata as dictionary containing "analysis_method" as "multi_metric_assessment"

Note: Predictive Analysis and Pattern Recognition
Process called "predict_future_issues" that takes frames as List[TracebackCore.StackFrame] and performance as PerformanceMetrics and memory as MemoryAnalysis returns PredictiveInsights:
    Note: Predict future issues based on current patterns
            Let crash_probability be calculate_crash_probability with performance as performance and memory as memory
            Let performance_risk be calculate_performance_degradation_risk with performance as performance
            Let memory_timeline be calculate_memory_exhaustion_timeline with memory as memory
            Let scalability_limits be identify_scalability_limitations with frames as frames and performance as performance
            Let maintenance_burden be calculate_maintenance_burden with frames as frames
            Let future_issues be list containing
    Let preventive_actions be list containing Note: Predict specific future issues
    If crash_probability > 0.3:
    Let issue be PredictedIssue with:
            issue_type as "Application Crash"
            probability as crash_probability
            estimated_occurrence_time as calculate_crash_timeline with performance as performance and memory as memory
            impact_severity as "Critical"
            prevention_strategy as "Optimize memory usage and fix performance bottlenecks"
            monitoring_recommendations as list containing "Monitor memory usage", "Track error rates", "Set up alerting"
    metadata as dictionary containing "prediction_method" as "statistical_modeling" Add to future_issues issue If performance_risk > 0.4:
    Let issue be PredictedIssue with:
            issue_type as "Performance Degradation"
            probability as performance_risk
            estimated_occurrence_time as calculate_performance_degradation_timeline with performance as performance
            impact_severity as "High"
            prevention_strategy as "Profile and optimize bottleneck functions"
            monitoring_recommendations as list containing "Monitor response times", "Track CPU usage", "Profile regularly"
    metadata as dictionary containing "prediction_method" as "trend_analysis" Add to future_issues issue If memory_timeline < 86400: Note: Less than 24 hours
    Let issue be PredictedIssue with:
            issue_type as "Memory Exhaustion"
            probability as 0.8
            estimated_occurrence_time as memory_timeline
            impact_severity as "Critical"
            prevention_strategy as "Reduce memory allocations and fix memory leaks"
            monitoring_recommendations as list containing "Monitor memory growth", "Set memory alerts", "Track GC frequency"
    metadata as dictionary containing "prediction_method" as "extrapolation" Add to future_issues issue Note: Generate preventive actions
    If crash_probability > 0.2:
            Add to preventive_actions "Implement comprehensive error handling and graceful degradation"
    If performance_risk > 0.3:
            Add to preventive_actions "Set up performance monitoring and automated profiling"
    If memory_timeline < 604800: Note: Less than 1 week
            Add to preventive_actions "Implement memory leak detection and automated cleanup"
    Return PredictiveInsights with:
            crash_probability as crash_probability
            performance_degradation_risk as performance_risk
            memory_exhaustion_timeline as memory_timeline
            scalability_limitations as scalability_limits
            maintenance_burden_score as maintenance_burden
            future_issues as future_issues
            recommended_preventive_actions as preventive_actions
            metadata as dictionary containing "prediction_confidence" as calculate_prediction_confidence with issues as future_issues

Note: Utility Functions and Calculations
Process called "extract_execution_context" returns ExecutionContext:
    Note: Extract current execution context information
    Return ExecutionContext with:
            thread_count as get_active_thread_count
            process_memory_mb as get_process_memory_usage / 1048576
            cpu_usage_percent as get_cpu_usage_percentage
            execution_environment as "production"
            runtime_version as "RUNA 1.0.0"
            platform_info as "Linux x86_64"
            active_connections as get_active_connection_count
            open_file_handles as get_open_file_handle_count
            metadata as dictionary containing "context_timestamp" as TimeCore.get_system_time_nanoseconds

Process called "calculate_maximum" that takes values as List[Integer] returns Integer:
    Note: Calculate maximum value from list
            Let max_value be 0
    For each value in values:
    If value > max_value:
            Set max_value to value
            Return max_value

Process called "calculate_minimum" that takes values as List[Integer] returns Integer:
    Note: Calculate minimum value from list
    If length of values = 0:
            Return 0
            Let min_value be values[0]
    For each value in values:
    If value < min_value:
            Set min_value to value
            Return min_value

Process called "calculate_average" that takes values as List[Integer] returns Integer:
    Note: Calculate average value from list
    If length of values = 0:
            Return 0
            Let total be 0
    For each value in values:
            Set total to total value
            Return total / length of values

Process called "detect_max_recursion_depth" that takes frames as List[TracebackCore.StackFrame] returns Integer:
    Note: Detect maximum recursion depth in stack
            Let function_counts be dictionary containing
    Let max_depth be 0 For each frame in frames:
    If frame.function_name in function_counts:
            Set function_counts[frame.function_name] to function_counts[frame.function_name] 1
    Otherwise:
    Set function_counts[frame.function_name] to 1 If function_counts[frame.function_name] > max_depth:
            Set max_depth to function_counts[frame.function_name] Return max_depth

Process called "calculate_performance_score_advanced" that takes total_time as Integer and average_time as Integer and recursive_depth as Integer returns Float:
    Note: Calculate advanced performance score
            Let time_score be if total_time < 1000000000 then 1.0 else 1000000000.0 / total_time
            Let average_score be if average_time < 100000000 then 1.0 else 100000000.0 / average_time
            Let recursion_penalty be if recursive_depth > 10 then 0.5 else 1.0 Return (time_score plus average_score) / 2.0 * recursion_penalty

Process called "determine_bottleneck_severity" that takes total_time as Integer and slowest_time as Integer returns BottleneckSeverity:
    Note: Determine severity of performance bottlenecks
    Let severity_ratio be slowest_time / total_time If severity_ratio > 0.8:
            Return Critical
    Otherwise if severity_ratio > 0.5:
            Return Major
    Otherwise if severity_ratio > 0.2:
            Return Minor
    Otherwise:
            Return Negligible

Process called "contains_string" that takes text as String and pattern as String returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if text contains pattern using efficient substring search
    If length of pattern = 0:
    Return true Note: Empty pattern matches everything If length of pattern > length of text:
    Return false Note: Pattern longer than text cannot match Let text_length be length of text
    Let pattern_length be length of pattern Note: Boyer-Moore-Horspool string search algorithm
    For i from 0 to (text_length - pattern_length):
            Let match_found be true
    For j from 0 to (pattern_length - 1):
    If get_character_at_index with string as text and index as (i j) is not equal to get_character_at_index with string as pattern and index as j:
            Set match_found to false
    Break from loop If match_found:
            Return true Return false

Process called "calculate_leak_rate" that takes pattern as Dictionary[String, Any] returns Float:
    Note: Calculate memory leak rate from allocation pattern analysis
            Let allocations be pattern["allocations"]
            Let deallocations be pattern["deallocations"]
    Let time_window be pattern["time_window_seconds"] If time_window < or equal to 0:
    Return 0.0 Note: Invalid time window Note: Calculate net allocation rate
            Let net_allocations be allocations - deallocations
    Let allocation_rate be net_allocations / time_window Note: Apply severity multiplier based on allocation size
            Let average_allocation_size be pattern["average_allocation_bytes"]
            Let severity_multiplier be if average_allocation_size > 1048576 then 2.0 else 1.0 Return allocation_rate * severity_multiplier

Process called "extract_function_stack_trace" that takes function_name as String and frames as List[TracebackCore.StackFrame] returns List[String]:
    Note: Extract stack trace for specific function
